thodological approaches for understanding the relationship between literature and visual culture.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aArt and literaturevHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aLiteraturexAestheticsvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 4aVisuelle Kultur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aLiterature.  aVisual arts.  aVisual culture.1 aAlbers, Irene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehrmann, Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenthien, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenthien, Claudia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBerndt, Frauke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBickenbach, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrosch, Renate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöger, Astrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrügh, Heinz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGil, Isabel Capeloa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKammer, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöhnen, Ralph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLöffler, Petra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNaumann, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeuber, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPuff, Helmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRehberg, Peter, econtrib